{"comments":"TypeScale - mathematical foundation for typographic hierarchy.\n\nA type scale is defined by:\n- **Base size**: The reference size (typically body text, e.g., 16px)\n- **Ratio**: The multiplier between adjacent scale steps\n\nSizes are calculated as: `base × ratio^step`\n\nStandard ratios derive from musical intervals:\n- **Minor Second** (1.067): 15/16 - subtle, conservative\n- **Major Second** (1.125): 8/9 - gentle progression\n- **Minor Third** (1.200): 5/6 - noticeable but not dramatic\n- **Major Third** (1.250): 4/5 - classic, balanced\n- **Perfect Fourth** (1.333): 3/4 - strong hierarchy\n- **Augmented Fourth** (1.414): √2 - geometric\n- **Perfect Fifth** (1.500): 2/3 - dramatic\n- **Golden Ratio** (1.618): φ - aesthetically pleasing\n\nExample: Base 16px with Major Third (1.250)\n- Step -2: 10.24px (small)\n- Step -1: 12.80px (footnote)\n- Step  0: 16.00px (body)\n- Step  1: 20.00px (h6)\n- Step  2: 25.00px (h5)\n- Step  3: 31.25px (h4)\n- Step  4: 39.06px (h3)\n- Step  5: 48.83px (h2)\n- Step  6: 61.04px (h1)\n- Step  7: 76.29px (hero)\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Typography","TypeScale"],"TypeScale"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[166,44],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TypeScale.purs","start":[166,1]},"title":"eqTypeScale"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Typography","TypeScale"],"TypeScale"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[170,44],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TypeScale.purs","start":[168,1]},"title":"showTypeScale"}],"comments":"Type scale definition\n\nCombines a base size with a ratio to generate a complete scale.\nSizes are calculated as: `base × ratio^step`\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[164,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TypeScale.purs","start":[161,1]},"title":"TypeScale"},{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Typography","TypeScale"],"ScaleRatio"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[95,46],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TypeScale.purs","start":[95,1]},"title":"eqScaleRatio"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Typography","TypeScale"],"ScaleRatio"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[98,61],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TypeScale.purs","start":[97,1]},"title":"showScaleRatio"}],"comments":"Scale ratio — the multiplier between adjacent type sizes\n\nNamed ratios derive from musical intervals, which produce\nnaturally harmonious progressions.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"data","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[93,30],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TypeScale.purs","start":[84,1]},"title":"ScaleRatio"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create a type scale\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Typography","FontSize"],"FontSize"],